locality: 2817CB Grid ref. Karasburg District, Aussenkjer 147 Farm, Plain towards Orange River.

South Africa, Northern cape, Richtersveld. On plain west of Ploegberg, 5 km south of Khubus. On coastal plain. Wel-drained sandy soil of granite-quartzite. Full sun. Native and abundant. Succulent Karoo. Perennial prostrate succulent, 20 cm high with branches of 50-60 cm covering the sand. Leaves opposite, simple, very succulent, cylindrical, 30-40 x 6-10 mm, mid-green. Flowers solitary, creamy white, petals 20 x 1 mm.
